chore: wave 9 polish — baseline-suggestion card, audit filters, lint debt, collector tests

Polish + cleanup pass on top of the wave 2-8 merge.

Shipped:
- New BaselineSuggestionsCard on the Drift page consumes the wave-8
  /api/v1/drift/baseline-suggestions endpoint. Fetches up to 5
  suggestions on mount, dismissable per browser session via
  sessionStorage, deep-links each suggestion to a pre-filtered drift
  query, surfaces muted vs accepted patterns with a pill, shows the
  active env tunables in the footer.
- Two new audit-log quick-filter pills: Auth (matches auth.sso_login,
  auth.scim_provisioned, auth.login_*) and Settings (settings.* events
  including webhook_signing_key_rotated). One-click for SOC reviewers
  to slice SSO + SCIM activity.

Lint debt cleared (lint went 9 errors + 3 warnings -> 0/0):
- Removed 3 unused @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any disable
  directives in envelope.ts and policy-service.ts.
- Fixed React Compiler purity error in SandboxBanner by bridging
  Date.now() through a per-minute ticker so render stays pure.
- Suppressed 6 react-hooks/set-state-in-effect errors with one-line
  justifications. All are load-on-mount + URL-to-state-sync +
  sessionStorage-on-mount patterns the rule prefers Suspense for;
  Suspense is a much bigger refactor and would fight existing page-
  level boundaries.

Test fixes (4 broken collector tests left over from wave-2 parser
additions, vitest now 191/191 across 28 files):
- parseSshConfig test now expects the always-emitted directive shape
  (port, x11Forwarding, maxAuthTries, permitEmptyPasswords,
  allowAgentForwarding, allowTcpForwarding all default to "unknown"
  when absent from sshd -T).
- collector-ssh.test.ts mock returns properly-framed BUNDLE_CMD
  output with all =BGS: sentinel sections instead of returning a
  flat string for individual subcommands.
- collector-ssh-failure.test.ts mock client gained a no-op destroy()
  to match the production code's error-path conn.destroy() call.

Verification: npm run lint clean, npm run typecheck clean, vitest
191/191 across 28 files.
